# 🚀 Day 51/90 – Development Roadmap: From Design to a Working MVP

Welcome to **Day 51!** 🎉

Over the past 50 days, we've designed almost every part of your Blood Report Analyzer.

Today we'll answer one question:

> **"If I started building tomorrow, what exactly should I build first?"**

This is how startups avoid building everything at once.

---

# 🎯 Today's Goal

By the end of today, you'll know:

* Which feature to build first
* Which features can wait
* What your first MVP should include
* How to release early
* How to improve after user feedback

---

# Step 1 – Build the Foundation

Don't start with AI.

Don't start with graphs.

Don't start with notifications.

Start with the foundation.

```text
User Registration

↓

Login

↓

Upload PDF

↓

Store PDF

↓

View Uploaded Reports
```

If this doesn't work, nothing else matters.

---

# Phase 1 – User Accounts

Complete these features first:

✅ Register

✅ Login

✅ Forgot Password

✅ Logout

✅ Profile

When these work, users can securely access their own reports.

---

# Phase 2 – Upload Reports

Next:

```text
Upload PDF

↓

Save PDF

↓

View PDF

↓

Delete PDF
```

At this stage, your app is basically a secure medical document vault.

That's okay.

---

# Phase 3 – OCR

Now connect OCR.

```text
PDF

↓

OCR

↓

Extract Text

↓

Find Blood Values
```

Don't worry about AI yet.

First, make sure OCR works reliably.

---

# Phase 4 – OCR Review

Users should verify extracted values.

```text
Hemoglobin

13.2

✏ Edit

Confirm
```

This improves accuracy before any AI explanation is generated.

---

# Phase 5 – AI Summary

Only after OCR is stable should you connect AI.

Flow:

```text
Confirmed Values

↓

AI

↓

Summary

↓

Display
```

Now your app becomes intelligent.

---

# Phase 6 – Report History

After AI:

```text
History

↓

Open Report

↓

Previous Reports

↓

AI Summary
```

Users can now build a health record over time.

---

# Phase 7 – Comparison

Now add:

```text
Report A

↓

Compare

↓

Report B
```

Show:

* Hemoglobin
* HbA1c
* Vitamin D

Side by side.

---

# Phase 8 – Trends

Finally:

```text
History

↓

Trend Graphs

↓

Health Timeline
```

This is where users begin seeing long-term improvements.

---

# What NOT to Build First

Many new founders make this mistake:

❌ Chatbot

❌ Dark Mode

❌ Themes

❌ Animations

❌ Fancy graphs

❌ Social sharing

These don't solve the core problem.

---

