Your first public version only needs:

```text
Login

↓

Upload PDF

↓

OCR

↓

User Review

↓

AI Summary

↓

History
```

That's enough to validate the idea with real users.

---

# Testing Checklist

Before release, verify:

```text
☑ Registration works

☑ Login works

☑ PDF uploads successfully

☑ OCR extracts values

☑ Users can edit values

☑ AI summary displays

☑ Reports are saved

☑ History opens correctly
```

---

# First User Feedback

Ask early users questions like:

* Was uploading easy?
* Did OCR extract the correct values?
* Was the AI explanation understandable?
* Which feature did you like most?
* What frustrated you?

Don't ask:

> "Do you like my app?"

Ask about specific experiences.

---

# Fix Before Adding Features

Suppose users report:

> OCR misses Vitamin D on some reports.

Fix OCR first.

Don't build:

* Dark Mode
* Notifications
* Graphs

Solve the biggest user problem before expanding the app.

